ce:section.ce:para:
To confirm the practicability of the proposed probe investigated for detecting of nicotine, the analysis was performed in real samples. For nicotine detection, 1−5 mM was spiked in the real (river and pond water) samples with good relative standard deviation (lower than 3.31 %) were obtained (
                              Table S5
                           ). Therefore, the proposed probe has potential applicability for nicotine detection in real samples and shows feasibility andcapability in the biological environment.

The calculated value of Eg is 2.48 eV, which fits well with the DRS data. N-CQDs can absorb a wider range of the spectrum and improve the light absorption efficiency because the band gap of N-CQDs is smaller than that of conventional g-C3N4 (2.67 eV) [50]. Additionally, CB of N-CQDs is estimated by VB and band gap data (
                           Table S4
                        ).
